fg_segments: Privacy policy How Convertworld.com uses cookies A cookie is a small piece of text sent to your browser by a website you visit.
It helps the website to remember information about your visit, like your preferred language and other settings.
This can make your next visit easier and the site more useful to you.

We use cookies for different purposes. We use them, for example, to remember your preferred home page converters, to remember your settings, to make the ads you see more relevant to you, to count how many visitors we receive to a page.
In compliance with EU directives about use of cookies, consent is needed from any European Union user.
This product includes GeoLite data created by MaxMind, available from http://www.maxmind.com.

Learn more about disable cookies in your web browser: If you sign up When you sign up for any of our services we will record specific personal information about you, such as your user name and email address.
You are responsible for keeping your password and user details confidential.
Nobody at Convertworld.com will ever ask you for your password, so please don't trust anybody asking you for it.
Measuring our visitors We measure visitors to our website using Google Analytics.
This records what pages you view within our site, how you arrived at our site and some basic information about your computer.
All of that information is anonymous – so we don't know who you are; just that somebody visited our site.
The information we collect from analytics helps us understand what parts of our sites are doing well, how people arrive at our site and so on.
Like most websites, we use this information to make our website better.
You can learn more about Google Analytics here: Learn about opting out: Advertisements Google AdSense is an advertising service provided by Google.
Convertworld.com uses this service, which tracks user behavior concerning ads.
You can learn more about Google AdSense here: Learn about opting out: Any questions?
Please contact us by using the link in the menu if you have any question about our privacy policy or your personal data.
